      • actionsInOrder

        public java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String> actionsInOrder(java.lang.String groupID)
        Gets an iterable over the ordered list of actions. for the specified group. The order of iteration matches the defined order.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        an iterable over the ordered list of groups.

      • addGroupID

        public void addGroupID(java.lang.String id)
        Adds a group id to the ordered list of groups. These should be added sequentially in the order in which the toolbar groups should be displayed.
        Parameters:
        id - the group id to add

      • addSeparator

        public void addSeparator()
        Adds a separator to the ordered list of groups. The separator will appear after the group given in the most recent call to addGroupID.

      • addActionID

        public void addActionID(java.lang.String groupID,
               java.lang.String actionID)
        Adds the actionID to the order list of actions for the specified group. These should be add sequentially in the order in which the actions should appear in the specified group.
        Parameters:
        groupID - the group to whose list of actions the actionID is added
        actionID - the id to add
